# JobPilot Core Rules

## Repository layout

- `backend/` — FastAPI (Python 3.11+), SQLAlchemy 2.0, PostgreSQL
- `frontend/` — Next.js 14 App Router, Tailwind CSS, TypeScript
- `docker-compose.yml` — local dev stack (postgres, backend, frontend)

## Security (never violate)

- Never commit `.env`, `.env.local`, `backend/.env`, or API keys
- Never commit the `docs/` folder (private planning docs)
- Use `.env.example` / `.env.local.example` with empty placeholder values only

## Workflow

- Use feature branches: `feat/<area>-<description>`
- Conventional commits: `feat(backend):`, `feat(frontend):`, `chore:`, `ci:`
- Open PRs into `main`; do not push secrets or docs/

## Stack conventions

- Backend routers under `/api/v1/`
- Job scrapers inherit from `JobSource` in `backend/app/scrapers/base.py`
- Frontend API client in `frontend/lib/api.ts`
- Dark UI: zinc-950 canvas, zinc-900 panels, indigo-600 accent
